HEADWORD: Impetrative
<hw>Im"pe*tra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impetrativus</ets> obtained by entreaty.]</ety> <def>Of the nature
of impetration; getting, or tending to get, by entreaty.</def>
